# Sample crontab entry: run the Ralph Loop tick every 5 hours.
#
# Cron is the low-ceremony alternative to the systemd timer (ralph.service +
# ralph.timer). Pick ONE, not both.
#
# INSTALL:
#   1. Edit the path below to your superproject (the repo that mounts ai-utils).
#   2. Append the line to your crontab:  crontab -e
#
# PREREQUISITES: `gh auth login` and `claude` must be authenticated for the user
# whose crontab this is. cron runs with a minimal environment, so we set a sane
# PATH and cd into the superproject first; adjust PATH if gh/claude/your toolchain
# live elsewhere.
#
# The tick is flock-guarded, so an overlapping fire is a harmless no-op.

PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin

# min hour dom mon dow  command
0 */5 * * *   cd /path/to/your/superproject && ai-utils/bin/ralph.sh >> .ralph.log 2>&1
